news.title: Kerala government to amend Land Assignment Act in upcoming assembly session
news.para: A Bill would be brought in the upcoming Assembly session beginning on January 23 to amend the Kerala Government Land Assignment Act, 1960. A high-level meeting, chaired by Chief Minister Pinarayi Vijayan, took a decision in this regard, according to a CMO statement.

news.title: Brick kilns back to work after penalty; Madras HC summons official
news.para: A special bench of Justice N Sathish Kumar and Justice D Bharatha Chakravarthy passed the interim order on a batch of pleas seeking closure and regulation of brick kilns located along the elephant corridors of Coimbatore.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body earns Rs 105 crore in property tax
news.para: Residents can clear their dues for the current fiscal with 10% penalty till March-end. However, people who are yet to clear their dues of previous years face the prospect of getting their properties sealed by the MC.

news.title: Eleven different fees may be levied besides impact fee in Ahmedabad
news.para: Apart from the impact fee, various other charges such as scrutiny fees, betterment charges, development charges, tree plantation fees, service and amenities fees and fire charges will have to be paid first.

news.title: Automatic name transfer system benefits 194 consumers in Nashik
news.para: The system is applicable only to old properties and is affected only after the change in the ownership has been completed by registration at the stamps and registration department of the state government.

news.title: New bylaws will be written for aviation hub near Noida airport
news.para: The airport, whose first phase is coming up on about a fifth of this area, is expected to be commissioned in October 2024. The bylaws will only address commercial establishments because there is no residential scheme within the aviation hub.

news.title: SC bars 'apartmentalization' of residential units in Chandigarh
news.para: A bench of Justices B R Gavai and B V Nagarathna slammed the Chandigarh administration for "blindly sanctioning" building plans and said it is apparent from them that they are in effect converting one dwelling unit into three apartments.

news.title: Gujarat government brings new rules to stop NRG property fraud
news.para: From now on, an NRG or individual residing outside the state, who delegates authority to their representatives to execute the sale of a property, will have to send an additional document declaring s/he was alive at the time of the sale.

news.title: NGT serves notice to agencies, government over flats on forest land in DLF-3
news.para: Retired Gurugram forest officer Rajinder Krishan Sharma and city resident Pawan Kumar Bansal alleged that 4,484 sqm of forest land in Sikanderpur-Nathupur Bundh area was diverted to build Ambience Island Lagoon Apartments in 2008 in defiance of the Forest Conservation Act, 1980.

news.title: CREDAI-NCR raise concerns over construction activities ban
news.para: Representatives of realtors body CREDAI-NCR met the minister to air their concerns and also submitted a memorandum highlighting the impact of the ban and suggesting possible solutions.

news.title: Delhi HC asks police to reply to Gopal Ansal's plea for renewal of passport
news.para: ​Justice Anup Jairam Bhambhani issued notice to the police and the Association of Victims of Uphaar Tragedy (AVUT) on the application of 74-year-old Gopal Ansal and asked them to file their replies within four weeks.

news.title: Gujarat HC upholds RERA's power to appoint commissioners
news.para: This case involved a project ‘Crystal Pramukh Commercial Hub’ in Vadodara by Keya Realty. The project began in 2013 and the developer sold 148 housing units of 376 without getting the project registered with RERA.

news.title: Licences cancelled two years ago, but 18 projects in Gurugram yet to be taken over by DTCP
news.para: As per a DTCP notification, a project can be taken over by the department for which licences have been cancelled. Following the takeover, a project can be completed either by the state government or through any third party.

news.title: Noida Authority to upload housing project details on site
news.para: The Authority has also decided to initiate action against the developers not yet ready to clear dues. On Monday, CEO Ritu Maheshwari directed the group housing department to upload the group housing details immediately.

news.title: China: Longfor Group Holdings' vice chairman resigns
news.para: The resignation follows former chairwoman, Wu Yajun, who stepped down in October and was replaced by Chen Xuping, 40, the company's chief executive.
